25|$|This period {{includes}} the <b>Sermon</b> <b>on</b> the Mount, {{one of the}} major discourses of Jesus in Matthew, and the <b>Sermon</b> <b>on</b> the Plain in the Gospel of Luke. The <b>Sermon</b> <b>on</b> the Mount, which covers chapters 5, 6 and 7 of the Gospel of Matthew, is the first of the Five Discourses of Matthew and is the longest piece of teaching from Jesus in the New Testament. It encapsulates many of the moral teaching of Jesus and {{includes the}} Beatitudes and the widely recited Lord's Prayer.|$|E
