25|$|While Matthew groups Jesus' teachings into sets {{of similar}} {{material}}, {{the same material}} is scattered when found in Luke. The <b>Sermon</b> <b>on</b> the Mount may {{be compared with the}} similar but more succinct <b>Sermon</b> <b>on</b> the Plain as recounted by the Gospel of Luke (6:17–49), which occurs at the same moment in Luke's narrative, and also features Jesus heading up a mountain, but giving the <b>sermon</b> <b>on</b> the way down at a level spot. Some scholars believe that they are the same sermon, while others hold that Jesus frequently preached similar themes in different places.|$|E
